    "section_image_with_text_ePUgyB": {
      "type": "section-image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "image_QrAAyX": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/41d-OP-SwingArm-BYB-background-August2020-900x600-1_50b1c1d9-aa7b-47b6-a7d1-30a26f959b40.png",
            "video": "",
            "video_button_color": "primary",
            "title": "",
            "desc": "<p>Here are just some of the reasons why a children’s playset is timeless and always a great investment: </p><h3>Children Love Them </h3><p>We’ve alluded to it already, but children of all ages love playsets. Whether a small model with swings or a large design with a climbing frame, slide, and other features, eyes light up when they see these colorful products. To them, a playset isn’t just a piece of playground equipment, it’s a ship, a bus, an adventure waiting to happen. <br/></p><h3>Physical Health </h3><p>Parents love a playset in Chicago because it means their child is staying active and healthy in a world of sitting in front of phones, tablets, and computers. Whether climbing or sliding, your child’s physical wellbeing is in great hands with a playset. </p><h3>Social Development </h3><p>When you have a playset in the backyard, it provides a brilliant opportunity for your children to play together, with friends, and others. Over time, this builds emotional intelligence and teamwork, skills that will follow them throughout childhood and into adulthood. </p><h3>Cognitive Development </h3><p>You may see a play slide and swing set, but children see a challenge. They want to navigate all the features, and interacting with the set requires them to overcome hurdles and think of creative solutions. </p><h3>Safety </h3><p>Finally, our wooden playsets and swing sets in Chicago, IL, come from Playground One, a leader in the field and a name known for safety. Their playsets offer 100% Pacific solid cedar, recessed nuts and bolts, double wall safety slides, non-slip gotcha grips, pinch-free safety swings, and many other brilliant features to keep your child happy and healthy. <br/></p>",
            "horizontal_align": "left",
            "link_title": "Learn more",
            "link": "",
            "bg_color_block": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "bg_color_content": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "color_text": "rgba(0,0,0,0)",
            "text_heading_color": true,
            "text_border_color": true
          }
        }
      },
